comments: Sabonis (SAC) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Sabonis (SAC) brings his hands toward Thompson (GSW) and marginal contact occurs as Sabonis (SAC) releases away from the contact.
Thompson (GSW) brings his arm toward Fox's (SAC) front and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Thompson (GSW) legally contests Fox's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Fox (SAC) does not overtly or abruptly extend his leg out as incidental contact occurs with Thompson (GSW) during the jump shot attempt.
Huerter (SAC) brings his hands towards Curry's (GSW) front and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Curry (GSW) is bracing for the contact from Huerter (SAC) and marginal contact occurs as Curry releases away.
Huerter (SAC) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Sabonis (SAC) is already in Green's (GSW) path and is firming up over his left leg when marginal contact occurs.
Thompson (GSW) is moving alongside Monk's (SAC) path and marginal body contact occurs during Monk's drive.
Monk (SAC) briefly grasps Thompson's (GSW) arm and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Green (GSW) is already in Fox's (SAC) path and is firming up when marginal contact occurs.
Huerter (SAC) brings his hand forward towards Curry's (GSW) front and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Huerter (SAC) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot attempt.

Replay review of the foul called on Thompson (GSW) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Thompson swipes his arm down and makes contact with Monk's (SAC) arm that causes him to lose control of the ball.  After communicating with the Replay Center, the call was changed from a shooting foul to a personal foul.
Huerter (SAC) and Wiggins (GSW) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Wiggins (GSW) moves through Sabonis (SAC) and dislodges him from his screening position.
Murray (SAC) legally contests Green's (GSW) shot near the rim.
Fox (SAC) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to the Warriors.
Curry (GSW) splits his feet at the start of his dribble.
Fox (SAC) and Curry (GSW) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs in the backcourt.
Metu (SAC) cleanly deflects the ball away from Curry (GSW) and Curry then legally regains possession.
Monk (SAC) turns into Curry's (GSW) body and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.
Mitchell (SAC) is moving alongside Curry's (GSW) path and marginal body contact occurs during the drive.
The foul is called on Metu (SAC) prior to a potential five second violation being committed by Curry (GSW).
Metu (SAC) brings his arms forward and initiates contact with Curry (GSW) in the post.
Thompson (GSW) makes contact with Huerter's (SAC) arm, which affects his jump shot attempt.
